  "title": "QUALITY ENGINEER (FOOD)",
  "description": "<p><strong>RESPONSIBILITIES AND DUTIES</strong>:</p><p>Implement food safety, quality control and quality assurance according to documented food safety and quality assurance programs. This is in line with achieving company food safety and quality policy.</p><p>·         Carrying out product sampling and testing basing on documented sampling plan</p><p>·         Conducting periodic inspection pertaining to GMP and safe food handling.</p><p>·         Conducting inspection pertaining to quality and process control by operation.</p><p>·         Carrying out incoming raw and packaging material inspection.</p><p>·         Tabulating statistical data for product quality performance index.</p><p>·         Assisting in in-house investigation of market complaint.</p><p>·         Arranging testing with third party laboratory testing service provider and following up test results.</p><p>·         Verifying laboratory testing document and costing.</p><p>·         Carrying out calibration of measuring instrument for production.</p><p>·         Assisting in all aspects of QA activities related to internal audits, customer audits, and regulatory inspection.</p><p>·         Supporting production with necessary quality evaluation of new products and project.</p><p>·         Maintaining in-house and customer document & records</p><p>·         Available to work a flexible schedule including evenings, weekends, and overtime</p><p><strong>Qualifications and experience needed:</strong></p><p>Must be knowledgeable about all food safety standards that are customary within the food industry and mandated by government regulations</p><p>1 to 3 years experience<br /></p>",
